    import fused

    utils = fused.load(

    # Load Census Block Group (CBG) table
    table_path_cbg = "s3://fused-asset/infra/census_block_us/"
    gdf_cbg = utils.table_to_tile(
        bbox,
        table=table_path_cbg,
        use_columns=[
            "STATEFP20",
            "COUNTYFP20",
            "TRACTCE20",
            "BLOCKCE20",
            "GEOID20",
            "NAME20",
            "geometry",
        ],
    )

    # Load Buildings (BLD) table
    table_path_bld = "s3://fused-asset/infra/building_msft_us"
    gdf_bld = utils.table_to_tile(
        bbox,
        table=table_path_bld,
        use_columns=["release", "capture_dates_range", "geometry"],
    )

    # Spatial JOIN between CBG with BLD
    # Determine CBG of each buildings
    gdf_joined = gdf_bld.sjoin(gdf_cbg, how="left", predicate="intersects")

    return gdf_joined

@fused.udf
def udf_vr():
    import fused
    import geopandas as gpd

    FILE_PATH = "https://www2.census.gov/geo/tiger/TIGER_RD18/STATE/11_DISTRICT_OF_COLUMBIA/11/tl_rd22_11_bg.zip"

    utils = fused.load(
        "https://github.com/fusedio/udfs/tree/f928ee1/public/common/"
    ).utils
    chip_shape = (256, 256)
    gdf = gpd.read_file(FILE_PATH)
    gdf = gdf.dissolve()
    minx, miny, maxx, maxy = gdf.total_bounds
    dx = (maxx - minx) / chip_shape[1]
    dy = (maxx - minx) / chip_shape[0]
    transform = [dx, 0.0, minx, 0.0, -dy, maxy, 0.0, 0.0, 1.0]
    geom = gdf.geometry.iloc[0]
    geom_mask = utils.rasterize_geometry(geom, chip_shape, transform)
    return geom_mask.astype("uint8") * 255  # , gdf.total_bounds
